# ── ROBBED_ · TESTNET (Robinhood Chain testnet, chain id 46630) ─────────────
# Build-time PUBLIC env for the testnet frontend (testnet.robbed.fun — the
# robbed-testnet Cloudflare Worker since 2026-07-12).
# All NEXT_PUBLIC_* are inlined at `next build`. No secrets here.
#
# Real testnet data. API_BASE_URL / WS_URL point at the testnet compose stack
# through Cloudflare Tunnel robbed_testnet. HOSTNAME NOTE (2026-07-12): the
# canonical API host is the FIRST-level `api-testnet.robbed.fun` — the earlier
# `api.testnet.robbed.fun` is a second-level subdomain outside Universal SSL's
# `*.robbed.fun` coverage and fails TLS at the edge (docker.md "Public
# exposure"); renamed rather than buying an Advanced Certificate.
NEXT_PUBLIC_CHAIN_ID=46630
NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_HTTP=https://rpc.testnet.chain.robinhood.com
# RPC WS deliberately UNSET: the only official WS *JSON-RPC* is the key-gated
# Alchemy endpoint (wss://robinhood-testnet.g.alchemy.com/v2/{KEY}, NEEDS-USER).
# NEVER wss://feed.testnet.chain.robinhood.com — that is the SEQUENCER FEED, a
# block feed, not JSON-RPC (docker-compose.testnet.yml header rule). Empty is
# tolerated (env.ts rpcWs ?? "") — viem stays on the HTTP transport.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_WS=
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=https://api-testnet.robbed.fun
NEXT_PUBLIC_WS_URL=wss://api-testnet.robbed.fun/ws
NEXT_PUBLIC_R2_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=https://pub-1f7ef06884964a2f82e21cd86e1893b0.r2.dev
# NEXT_PUBLIC_WALLETCONNECT_PROJECT_ID=   # set your WalletConnect project id
# NEXT_PUBLIC_LARGE_VALUE_ETH_THRESHOLD=1.0

# RESOLVED 2026-07-12: the web now reads NEXT_PUBLIC_CHAIN_ID (validated
# against the shared deployment registry, — env selects, registry
# defines) and derives chain facts (name/explorer) + ALL addresses (robbed six,
# V3 set, WETH) from the 46630 registry entry (/ T-3 codegen). This file
# is NOT auto-loaded by `next dev`/`next build` (Next only loads .env,
# .env.local, .env.$(NODE_ENV)[.local]) — it is the value sheet for the
# testnet Workers build vars; the compose testnet stack injects the same values
# via docker-compose.testnet.yml `web.environment`.
